<TITLE> Pakistan fill Australia void by hosting Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, March 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan will fill the void caused by the postponement of the Australia tour by hosting Bangladesh next month. Bangladesh have agreed to play five one-dayers and a Twenty20 match from April 6 to 22, the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) said on Tuesday. PCB chief operating officer Shafqat Naghmi also told reporters the board was holding talks about hosting a one-day series with Sri Lanka in April and May. "They (Sri Lanka) are keen to come and help us out," said Naghmi. "We are confident of finalising the itinerary shortly." Australia postponed their tour because of the troubled security situation in Pakistan. Bangladesh are to play their first two games in Lahore followed by matches in Multan, Faisalabad and Karachi. The Twenty20 game will also take place in Karachi
